Layer normalization is a technique that significantly impacts the performance and training stability of large language models (LLMs). It involves normalizing inputs rather than outputs (referred to as "pre-norm") to stabilize training. Some models, like BLOOM and Alexa, add an extra layer normalization before the embedding layer to further enhance stability in large-scale training.
